        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "9tn3w",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "user",
                                "user_id": "U012XRK1371"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "So, the idea is to structure the web application as set of pre-defined concepts?\nThen these concepts are composed together declaratively as a html tree data structure (coded by someone or generated by composer UI).\nAnd under the hood, there is something that coordinates the client-server communication (by handling eval\/exec), with possible transaction like synchronization for certain events?"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Yes, that is correct.\n\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "I think of concept as a “process” (that runs on frontend\/backend) with eval and exec operations. "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Yes, that’s good. Note that a concept can have multiple eval\/exec operations (one set of eval\/exec per concept component)\n\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "So if I have two concepts, how can I combine them?"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\nFor example, let’s say you have a book review app and you’d like to allow your users to input book reviews with a comment and a star rating. So, you create a review component and include the "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "create-comment",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " component of the "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "comment",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " concept and the "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "rate-target",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " component of the "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "rating",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " concept:\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "...\n<comment.create-comment \/>\n<rating.rate-target \/>\n..."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "At this point, your users can create a review comment and a rating separately, but we want to compose them and have the exec run together, so we do two things: (1) we wrap them with a "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "dv.tx",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "; and (2) we wire a generated  unique ID to both concept components so that the entities they eventually save (the rating and comment) are linked by the shared ID:\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "...\n<dv.tx>\n  <dv.gen-id \/>\n  <comment.create-comment id=dv.gen-id.id targetId=$postId \/>\n  <rating.rate-target targetId=dv.gen-id.id \/>\n  <dv.button \/>\n<\/dv.tx>\n..."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " When the user clicks on the "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "dv.button",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ", both the "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "exec",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " of "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "create-comment",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "  and the "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "exec",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " of "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "rate-target",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " run together at the same time."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
